cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.NA

The paper focuses on performance optimization and modeling of parallel programming in UPC, which is a language for parallel computing. This makes it likely to fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. Additionally, the paper discusses performance models and hardware characteristics, which could also place it under the Performance (cs.PF) category. The use of UPC and parallel computing also suggests a possible fit for the Architecture (cs.AR) category. The paper also discusses strategies for enhancing performance, which could place it under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category. Finally, the paper discusses the solution of a 2D heat equation, which could place it under the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) category.
